[[Arya Samaj]] was established in [[Uganda]] in 1908 by Pandit Purnanand.{{citation needed|date=May 2012}} In 1929 a large building was constructed by the Samaj. The Uganda Arya Samaj was one of the most active in [[East Africa]] until the political revolution led by [[Idi Amin]] forced all the people of [[India]]n origin to leave Uganda and the work of Arya Samaj came to an end.

