{{Portal|Catholicism}} The '''Bishop of Kerry''' is the [[Ordinary (officer)|Ordinary]] of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Kerry]], one of the suffragan dioceses of the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Cashel and Emly|Archdiocese of Cashel and Emly]] in [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]].<ref name=dkerr>{{Catholic-hierarchy|diocese|dkerr|Diocese of Kerry |18 May 2009}}</ref>
The [[Episcopal see]] changed its name from [[Bishop of Ardfert and Aghadoe|Ardfert and Aghadoe]] to Kerry on 20 December 1952.<ref name=dkerr/> The bishop's seat ([[Cathedra]]) is located at the [[St Mary's Cathedral, Killarney|Cathedral Church Saint Mary, Killarney]].
The current bishop is the Most Reverend [[Raymond Browne]] who was [[Appointment of Catholic bishops|appointed]] Bishop of Kerry by [[Pope Francis]] on 2 May 2013 and received [[Consecration#Roman Catholic Church|episcopal consecration]] at St Mary's Cathedral, Killarney on 21 July 2013.
