{{Infobox temple | name = Hindu Temple of Central Indiana | image = Hindu Temple of Central Indiana.jpg | alt = | caption = | map_type = USA Indiana | map_caption = Location in Indiana | coordinates = {{coord|39.818597|-85.973448|type:landmark_region:US-IN|display=inline,title}} | other_names = | proper_name = | country = United States | state = [[Indiana]] | location = [[Indianapolis, Indiana|Indianapolis]] | elevation_m = | deity = | primary_deity_Godess = | utsava_deity_God = | utsava_deity_Godess= | Direction_posture = | Pushakarani = | Vimanam = | Poets = | Prathyaksham = | festivals= | address = | architecture = | temple_quantity = | monument_quantity= | inscriptions = | year_completed = 2006 | creator = | website = {{URL|https://www.htci.org//}} }}
{{Hinduism small}}
'''Hindu Temple of Central Indiana (HTCI)''' is a [[hindu temple]] located in [[Indianapolis]]. The temple is currently located at 3350 N. German Church Rd in the middle of several cornfields<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.pbs.org/show/temple-makers/|title = Temple Makers|website = PBS|access-date = 27 October 2018}}</ref>.
==History== Before the creation of HTCI, most hindus would go to [[Hindu Temple of Dayton]] or temples in Chicago for hindu worship services. Members of the Hindu Community in the [[Indianapolis Metropolitan Area]] decided to create a Hindu Temple which was inaugurated in 2006. In 2011, HTCI held a ceremony for its new idols, Sri Subramanya and Sri Ayyappa<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.eurasiareview.com/24032012-hindu-temple-of-central-indiana-holding-elaborate-3-day-consecration-ceremony/|title = Hindu Temple of Central Indiana Holding Elaborate 3 Day Consecration Ceremony|website = eurasiareview|date = 24 March 2012|access-date = 27 October 2018}}</ref>.
In June 2015, the temple's $10 Million worship hall was opened. The worship hall contains 17 shrines to various Hindu Deities spread over 4 different [[Gopurams]], with the main tower being over 99 feet tall<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.indystar.com/story/news/2015/03/17/expansion-indy-hindu-temple-open-june/24939491/|website = indystar|title = $10M expansion of Indy Hindu temple to open in June|date = 18 March 2015|access-date = 27 October 2018|author = Wang, Stephanie}}</ref>.
